OL,3,CPeople warned to boil water as disease
OL,4,Ccases confirmed
OL,6,FPeople living in parts of Devon are
OL,7,Fbeing warned to boil tap water after
OL,8,Fmultiple cases of cryptosporidium were
OL,9,Fconfirmed.
OL,11,FThe UK Health Security Agency has
OL,12,Fconfirmed 22 cases of the parasite,
OL,13,Fwhich causes a diarrhoea-type illness,
OL,14,Fin the Brixham area. There have been a
OL,15,Ffurther 70 reported cases of vomiting
OL,16,Fand diarrhoea.
OL,18,FThe government says the disease is
OL,19,Fpredominantly waterborne and
OL,20,Finfections can be caused by drinking
OL,21,Fcontaminated water.
